{"title_page": "There's Really a Wolf", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = There's Really a Wolf\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Russ (rapper)|Russ]]\n| cover      = RussThere'sReallyaWolf.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = May 5, 2017\n| recorded   = 2015\u20132017\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| length     = 63:50\n| label      = {{hlist|Russ My Way Inc.|[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]}}\n| producer   = [[Russ (rapper)|Russ]] (also [[Executive producer#Music|exec]].)\n| prev_title = How to Rob\n| prev_year  = 2014\n| next_title = [[Zoo (Russ album)|Zoo]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = There's Really a Wolf\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Pull the Trigger\n | single1date = July 28, 2015\n | single2     = [[What They Want (Russ song)|What They Want]]\n | single2date = August 19, 2015\n | single3     = [[Losin Control]]\n | single3date = November 9, 2015\n | single4     = Do It Myself\n | single4date = December 31, 2015\n | single5     = Me You\n | single5date = June 6, 2017<ref name=\"FutureReleases\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases|title=Top 40 Rhythmic Future Releases|work=AllAccess|accessdate=May 20, 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''There's Really a Wolf''''' is the twelfth studio album and major-label debut by American rapper [[Russ (rapper)|Russ]], who composed and produced all of the songs. It was released on May 5, 2017, by Russ My Way Inc. and [[Columbia Records]] and peaked at number seven on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and number four on the US [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]]<ref name=\"Amaya Mendizabal\">{{citeweb|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7800899/russ-theres-really-a-wolf-top-rb-hip-hop-albums-chart-top-five|title=Russ' 'There's Really a Wolf' Debuts at No. 4 on Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums Chart|author=Amaya Mendizabal|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=May 18, 2017|accessdate=May 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/theres-really-a-wolf/id1226725825|title=There's Really A Wolf|accessdate=May 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/theres-really-a-wolf-mw0003042635/credits|title=There's Really a Wolf - Russ - Credits - AllMusic|website=AllMusic|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> On April 18, 2018, it was certified [[Recording Industry Association of America certification|Platinum]].\n\n{{ external media\n| align  = right\n| video1 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IdGIZjVWrzY Russ - Losin Control (Official Video)] (February 1, 2016)\n| video2 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oorK4RPgZ8Q Russ - What They Want (Official Video)] (May 3, 2016)\n| video3 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BYbOkRye4gs Russ - Do It Myself (Official Video)] (June 7, 2016)\n| video4 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wjh2gav5a48 Russ - Pull The Trigger (Official Video)] (July 17, 2016)\n}}\n\n==Promotion==\nThe album was announced on April 19, 2017, with a tweet revealing the album's release date of May 5, 2017.\n\n==Singles==\nAll but four of the songs on the album were brand new releases that Russ had recorded and saved from the public eye for a span of two years. The previous released tracks \"[[What They Want (Russ song)|What They Want]]\", \"Pull the Trigger\", \"Do It Myself\", and the R&B track \"[[Losin Control]]\", were all originally released on [[SoundCloud]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Russ SoundCloud|url=https://soundcloud.com/russ|website=SoundCloud|accessdate=8 May 2017}}</ref> \"Me You\" was sent to rhythmic radio as the third single on June 6, 2017.<ref name=\"FutureReleases\"/>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''There's Really a Wolf'' debuted at number seven on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and number four on the US [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]] charts moving 49,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s in its first week of release.<ref name=\"Amaya Mendizabal\"/> On April 18, 2018, the album was certified [[RIAA Certification|platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) for combined sales and [[album-equivalent unit]]s of over a million units in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/?s=There+Really+is+a+wolf|title=Gold & Platinum - RIAA|website=riaa.com|accessdate=1 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll tracks written and produced by [[Russ (rapper)|Russell James Vitale]].<ref>https://listen.tidal.com/artist/18318625</ref><ref name=\"AllMusic\">{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/theres-really-a-wolf-mw0003042635|title=There's Really a Wolf - Russ - Songs, Reviews, Credits - AllMusic|website=AllMusic|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| title1 = I'm Here\n| length1 = 3:59\n\n| title2 = The Stakeout\n| length2 = 2:51\n\n| title3 = Act Now\n| length3 = 3:09\n\n| title4 = Cherry Hill\n| length4 = 3:42\n\n| title5 = Me You\n| length5 = 2:44\n\n| title6 = Ride Slow\n| length6 = 3:05\n\n| title7 = Don't Lie\n| length7 = 3:08\n\n| title8 = Do It Myself\n| length8 = 2:47\n\n| title9 = I Wanna Go Down with You\n| length9 = 3:03\n\n| title10 = Family & Friends\n| length10 = 2:55\n\n| title11 = [[What They Want (Russ song)|What They Want]]\n| length11 = 2:45\n\n| title12 = Got This\n| length12 = 2:52\n\n| title13 = No Turning Back\n| length13 = 2:34\n\n| title14 = [[Losin Control]]\n| length14 = 3:57\n\n| title15 = Scared\n| length15 = 2:59\n\n| title16 = Back to You\n| length16 = 3:27\n\n| title17 = One More Shot\n| length17 = 3:11\n\n| title18 = Emergency\n| length18 = 3:50\n\n| title19 = Pull the Trigger\n| length19 = 2:36\n\n| title20 = MVP\n| length20 = 4:16\n\n| total_length  = 63:50\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[AllMusic]].<ref name=\"AllMusic\"/>\n\n* Colm Dillane \u2013 art direction, design\n* [[Russ (rapper)|Russ]] \u2013 primary artist, executive producer, composer, engineer, mastering, mixing, producer, guitar, piano, ukulele\